cising, especially with heavier loads. Some Smith machines include multiple workout stations being all-in-one trainers, while others are basic Smith machine units.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1687471845906" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1687471845906"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">The Origin of the Smith Machine</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1687471863834" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1687471863834"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Let's dive into the Smith's machine history that starts in the 1950s when a sports and nutrition expert Jack LaLanne decided to create equipment that will help people to squat safely without anyone's support. He told bodybuilder and gym owner Rudy Smith about his intention, who finally crafted a machine by changing the initial design, with the help of Vic Tanny and Paul Martin who made the proper design for the future Smith machine that appeared in the fitness gyms.</p><p>Nowadays, the Smith machine is a popular gym tool for various lifts without a spotter. This equipment is a great option both for commercial and home gyms to perform exercises such as bench presses, squats, deadlifts, rows, lunges, etc.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1682453685529" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1682453685529" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/8d7b218f-d8db-4219-a83a-6627ea9d5b2a/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/athlete-smith-machine-workout.jpg" alt="athlete smith machine workout" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="798" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="athlete smith machine workout" natural-width="1200" natural-height="798"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1687471871686" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1687471871686" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">What Muscles Are Worked Out During the Smith Machine Training?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1687471885448" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1687471885448"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Smith machine is a highly versatile equipment that can become an effective tool to build lean muscle mass and boost your strength. You can perform numerous exercises on it, almost the same way as with a standard bar. That makes it possible to target all major muscle groups, i.e., quadriceps, glutes, back muscles, as well as the supporting such as hamstrings and spinal erectors, and stabilizing muscles that are abdominals and calves.</p><p>The Smith machine targets the following muscles:</p><ul><li><strong>Back muscles</strong>. Lower back muscles (lumbar region) will be strengthened while squatting with a proper form. Spinal erectors will be activated to keep your back straight and engaged in the movement. For instance, performing a Romanian deadlift targets the entire posterior chain muscles. Smith machines shrugs work out well your trapezius, while bent-over rows are appropriate for isolating your traps, lats, and rhomboids. Upright rows will be good for your traps too.</li><li><strong>Chest</strong>. Bench presses are highly effective for building up a group of muscles such as chest, front delts, and triceps. Incline bench presses are also effective in developing defined chest muscles.</li><li><strong>Arms</strong>. Deadlifts can be useful for strengthening your forearms, while a shoulder press is good for your triceps. Bicep curls are perfect for biceps, brachioradialis, and forearm flexors.</li></ul></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1687474490807" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1687474490807"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><ul><li><strong>Core</strong>. Your <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/223081770_Back_and_abdominal_muscle_function_during_stabilization_exercises" class="" target="_blank">core works to stabilize your movements</a>. Your abs will work at a much less rate (approximately 40-50% less). Smith machine crunches, sit-ups target rectus abdominis, transverse abdominis, and oblique side bends are good for obliques.</li><li><strong>Legs</strong>. Your quads, especially your front thighs, will be more activated with a narrower and deeper position. The glute muscles will receive a greater load the wider you place your feet. Hip adductors (inside of your thighs) will be involved the lower you squat. The hamstrings are involved in knee flexion and hip extension. You can perform such conventional yet effective exercises like back squats, split squats, lunges, Bulgarian split squats, etc.</li></ul></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1687474410772" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1687474410772" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/aa04ea17-d5d7-495f-9881-664bdcf3a5c5/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/athlete-smith-machine.jpg" alt="athlete smith machine muscle training" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="athlete smith machine muscle training" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1685566177601" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1685566177601"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Why Buy the Smith Machine?</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1685565818895" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1685565818895" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>If you want to pump up your muscle size and strength capabilities safely, a Smith machine will allow you to do it. This tool brings more pros compared to free-weight training and other resistance machines such as lat pulldown, leg press, or shoulder press machines.</p><p>Although, don't prioritize training just with the Smith machine over other equipment and free weights. Keep your training regime diverse and balanced in focus on all muscles, by using various gym tools and machines to provide your body with a universal workout that targets the whole body.</p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1685574207747" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1685574207747"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">1. Building Muscle Mass Gradually</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1659008080564" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1659008080564" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>No matter whether you're a novice or a seasoned lifter, this gym machine will come in handy to build and enhance muscle tissue's gradual growth without injuries. Additionally, you'll be able to learn proper weightlifting movement techniques: you'll know how <a href="https://journals.lww.com/nsca-jscr/Fulltext/2009/12000/A_Comparison_of_Free_Weight_Squat_to_Smith_Machine.23.aspx" class="" target="_blank">to execute squats</a>, presses, and lunges correctly. By working out on the Smith machine you'll be able to train the key lower and upper body muscles, but with a fixed vertical range of motion without falling backward and forward.</p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1685574196774" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1685574196774"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">2. Deloading the Stabilizing Muscles</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1659008080570" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1659008080570" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Since the Smith machine comes with a fixed-path resistance mechanism, the bar is locked in a fixed position, namely, it moves just in a straight line. So, you don't have to activate your muscles-stabilizers just like with a free-weight workout. All the load comes to the primary muscles without involving smaller supporting ones.</p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1687474517583" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1687474517583" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/afa9e778-1736-4d02-8ebb-a8bfed8d3ebc/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/smith-machine-in-gym.jpg" alt="smith machine in gym" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="smith machine in gym" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1685574186909" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1685574186909"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">3. Lifting Greater Weights for a Longer Time</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1682451480043" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1682451480043" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>With a Smith machine, you can work out with heavier loads because this tool has a barbell fixed in a one-motion line and slides up and down and you don't have to activate small stabilizing muscles to perform barbell back squats or barbell bench presses. The weight is fixed in one position which eliminates the need to involve all your strength and power to do these exercises, unlike with free-weight ones.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1686776799710" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1686776799710"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">4. More Focus on the Exercise Itself</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1682451509569" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1682451509569" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Thanks to the fact that the barbell is located securely on the slide rail and moves up and down, an athlete can concentrate on the proper exercise technique. There's no need to worry about maintaining balance while holding the weights since the bar is totally fixed, which also brings you better stability, especially if you're a starter at lifting weights.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1685574178536" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1685574178536"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">5. Maintaining Proper Posture</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1686776811811" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1686776811811" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>As a barbell is fixed and you don't have to involve stabilizing muscles to lift the weight, you can focus on your technique and keep your back straight with a slight incline. Hence, you can control your posture with each rep and form through all the possible ranges of motion. It enables you to move naturally and reduces the possibility of injury.</p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1687472165920" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1687472165920"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">6. High Rate of Safety</h3></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1659008080577" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1659008080577" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass="" data-layout-lg="12" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1658828961229" data-id="1658828961229"><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1687472169319" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1687472169319" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The Smith machine is equipped with multiple hooks at different heights to rack a barbell securely if an athlete can't lift the loads anymore and wants to quit the exercise. This is a good safety mechanism for those who train on their own or don't want a spotter to look at their performance technique. Also, it's an opportunity for them to push themselves harder to increase strength and avoid getting the weights back.</p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1685572722442" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1685572722442" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/120f16f0-60d6-43a9-85bb-c4d89c882ca3/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/male-smith-machine-exercise.jpg" alt="male smith machine exercise" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="798" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="male smith machine exercise" natural-width="1200" natural-height="798"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1659008080579" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1659008080579"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">How to Pick a Smith Machine?</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1686776882690" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1686776882690" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Professional lifters and avid bodybuilders know the essence of the Smith machine and adore it for its versatility. What’s more, even beginners and intermediate gym attendees learn new exercises eagerly on this gym equipment. Let's shed light on this gym machine and outline the key features you should know when looking for a high-quality Smith machine, or if not buying it, simply what points to focus on when choosing it at the local gym to work out.</p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1685574155957" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1685574155957"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">1. Dimensions</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1659008080583" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1659008080583" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>If you want to complement your home gym with such a functional machine, the first thing you should pay attention to is its size. The Smith machine shouldn't be too hefty, but more compact not to take the spare place in your gym room and the living space left. Mind the footprint especially if you find a Smith machine that unites several trainers in one piece of equipment, becoming a multipurpose workout station.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1685574146070" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1685574146070"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">2. Functionality</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1659008080584" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1659008080584" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Many of the Smith machine models are equipped with benches, power rack stations, various attachments for low rows, pull-ups, dips, suspension trainers, etc. These options make the machine a universal all-in-one trainer for working out different muscles. So, apparently, there's no need to join the gym.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1685574134685" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1685574134685"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">3. Weight Ratio</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1659008080586" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1659008080586" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Generally, all Smith machines come with pulley systems with varying weight ratios - 1:1 and 2:1. The first option means that the loaded weight is the exact weight you will feel while lifting. A 2:1 ratio is when you'll lift half of the real weight. For example, with a 2:1 ratio, if you load 200 pounds, you will lift 100 pounds.</p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1687474655676" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1687474655676" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/7bfaf91e-31f4-4e9f-8e93-d5a2269e8777/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/smith-machine-review.jpg" alt="smith machine review" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="smith machine review" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1685574098197" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1685574098197"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">4. Good-Quality Linear Bearing</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1659008080587" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1659008080587" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The majority of Smith machines move in a vertical line, so linear bearings are highly important because they ensure that the steel bar won't vibrate or get stuck during lifting weights. In general, you can find linear bearing sleeves on both sides of the tool which are attached to the bar. This point greatly affects bar smooth motion since this mechanism assists athletes to pull heavier weights.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1686776955285" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1686776955285"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">5. Safety Mechanism</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1686776962849" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1686776962849" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The Smith machine is a perfect tool for those who just started training with weights. It can help in <a href="https://journals.lww.com/nsca-jscr/Fulltext/2020/07000/Effects_of_Training_With_Free_Weights_Versus.6.aspx" class="" target="_blank">resistance and free weight training</a> by enabling inexperienced athletes to rack the bar at any moment during the set. Such a safety mechanism can look like locking pins that prevent the bar move below a specific depth; spring <a href="https://torokhtiy.com/blogs/reviews/best-barbell-collars" class="" target="_blank">clamps</a> to secure the weight plates during the workout; catch rods fastened inside the frame at the bar glide pathway to ensure you can stop doing lifts when you're enough; hooks and bar catches. All these attachments are important since they can prevent injuries and add some confidence to an athlete while exercising with greater loads.</p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1687472321715" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1687472321715"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">6. Availability of Counterbalance System</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1687472338080" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1687472338080" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The fact is that not all Smith machines come with a counterbalance system. What is it? A counterbalance system may come with diverse attachments, i.e., pulleys, cables, rods, extra bushings, and counterweights that can be placed within the frame/ rack situated to the bar. So, when pulling the bar during the exercise, it decreases its weight. The key target of this system is to reduce the bar weight and get a lighter weight at the start. This option is useful for working out small or weak muscles.</p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678924878616" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1678924878616" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/9732177b-2ce6-48ba-be49-dfe8c69f6f56/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/man-stance-on-smith-machine.jpg" alt="man stance on smith machine" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="man stance on smith machine" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1687472354718" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1687472354718"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Top Exercises to Perform Using the Smith Machine</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1687472365787" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1687472365787" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Imagine this bulky piece of equipment that looks like a rack with a fixed barbell on the steel rails gliding up and down. It can be quite a hefty and daunting gym machine, but actually, it's elementary to work out and get benefits from it.</p><p>If you’re using this gym machine for the first time, you should adjust it to your height and choose the proper weights according to your capabilities to reap the benefits of training. The first thing you should do is place a barbell at an appropriate height that will be convenient for performing particular exercises. Also, if you need to use a bench, you should fix it right, i.e., adjust the seat height and change the backrest position - set it angled for doing a chest press or chest fly exercises, or leave the back pad flat for bench press training. The rest of the Smith machine’s accessories can’t be adjusted manually since this is a single construction with built-in components. So, to get a Smith machine that fits your height and room space, consider its dimensions before the purchase.</p><p>You can use the Smith machine for dozens of exercises to challenge your whole body with any weight, yet get extra support and balance. These exercises are common ones that you can make a good thing of:</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1687472391978" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1687472391978"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">1. For legs:</h3></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1687472481936" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1687472481936"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h4 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>Back squats</b></h4></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1687472534659" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1687472534659" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>First, you'll succeed to target the quadriceps, glutes, and also engage the core muscles. Secondly, being a conventional exercise, you'll improve your squatting technique by keeping your back straight and being able to control the squat depth. Also, you'll get extra stability.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1687474922240" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1687474922240" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_module--md gf_module--sm gf_module--xs {{extraClass}}"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/QcmonZUuumg" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1687474928179" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1687474928179" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><strong style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">How to perform</strong><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">: place the bar on your shoulders and traps, keep your feet 3 inches in front of the bar hip-width apart. Keep your back straight and </span><a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/7881749_Trunk_Muscle_Activity_Increases_With_Unstable_Squat_Movements" class="" target="_blank" style="font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: white;">core tight</a><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">, slowly hinge your hips back until your thighs become parallel to the floor. Keep your feet flat and push yourself back through the heels up to the start position. Don’t round the back, avoid knee inward collapse, don’t lift the heels off the floor, and look too high.</span><br></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1687472593533" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1687472593533"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h4 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>Bulgarian Split Squats</b></h4></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1687472597395" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1687472597395" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Here you'll work out your glutes and quadriceps well. The Smith machine will help you not to wobble occasionally if losing your balance, so you'll manage to lean on a bent leg securely.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1687474996293" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1687474996293" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_module--md gf_module--sm gf_module--xs {{extraClass}}"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/VLKRDM6sxrc" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1687475004470" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1687475004470" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><strong style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">How to perform</strong><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">: place a bench behind the bar. Put the bar on your traps and shoulders, elevate one leg behind you on the bench, with a standing leg 3-4 inches in front of the bar. Lower your back knee to the floor slowly, with the front knee bent to 90 degrees.</span><br></p><p>Push yourself back by involving your glutes and front leg and return to the start position. Keep your back straight and core tight. Bring the load to the front leg and push it with your strong glute muscles.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1687472645356" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1687472645356"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">2. For Arms and Chest:</h3></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1687472633099" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1687472633099"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h4 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>Close Grip Bench Press</b></h4></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1687472665950" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1687472665950" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>You'll train mainly pectoral muscles and triceps. If you're a beginner at lifting weights and have weak chest muscles or arms, the Smith machine will be useful in this case.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1687475091931" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1687475091931" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_module--md gf_module--sm gf_module--xs {{extraClass}}"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/0TPkV7AXX8o" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1687475096521" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1687475096521" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><strong style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">How to perform</strong><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">: lay on a bench, hook the bar with a close grip with your arms fully lengthened. 